      "content": "okay i get that, but like, if you had to pick a starting point for a philosophical foundation, wouldn't the humanitarian argument be stronger because human rights are supposed to be universal/absolute, whereas border laws are just something countries make up? it feels like one is a fundamental truth and the other is just policy.",
